globalDetailRoute(25.10)                              globalDetailRoute(25.10)

Name  globalDetailRoute - Uses the NanoRoute router to perform both global and
       detailed routing with one command
Syntax
Parameters <area> Specifies the coordinates (x1 y1 x2 y2) of the bounding  box
       area  for  detailed  routing.  The  entire  design  is globally routed.
       Data_type: rect, optional -help Outputs a brief  description  that  in-
       cludes  the type and default information for each globalDetailRoute pa-
       rameter. For a detailed description of the command and all of its para-
       meters, use the man command: man globalDetailRoute -select  Routes  se-
       lected nets. To select a net, use the selectNetcommand or click the net
       in  the  design display window. Tip: You can also specify setNanoRoute-
       Mode  -route_selected_net_only  true  to  route  the   selected   nets.
       Data_type: bool, optional
Example
